Sentencas: Biogas (60%-CH4, 40%- CO2) is a potential source of renewable energy when used as energy feedstock for solid oxide fuel cells (SOFC), but releases biogenic CO2 emissions.
Titulo: Biohythane as an energy feedstock for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Hybrid SOFC performance can be affected by fuel composition and reformer performance.
Titulo: Biohythane as an energy feedstock for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Biohythane (58%-CH4, 35%-CO2 and 7% H-2) can be a better alternative providing balance between energy and biogenic emissions.
Titulo: Biohythane as an energy feedstock for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Biohythane performance is studied for a 120 kW SOFC stack using ASPEN process model and compared with other feed stocks.
Titulo: Biohythane as an energy feedstock for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: This work is the first to study and report on the application of biohythane in SOFC systems.
Titulo: Biohythane as an energy feedstock for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Biohythane was found to produce less biogenic CO2 emissions and 6% less CO at the reformer than biogas.
Titulo: Biohythane as an energy feedstock for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Comparisons show that biohythane provides better efficiencies in hybrid SOFC systems.
Titulo: Biohythane as an energy feedstock for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Sensitivity studies recommends operation of stack with biohythane at Steam to Carbon Ratio (STCR) = 2.0, i = 200 mA cm(-2) and U-F = 0.85 respectively.
Titulo: Biohythane as an energy feedstock for solid oxide fuel cells
